This paper deals with natural language inference (NLI) datasets and sentence representation evaluation, which are topics that fall under the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). However, since the focus is on NLI and language understanding, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.AI and cs.LG. The other two sub-categories are less likely but still relevant due to the potential applications of NLI in computer vision and natural language processing.
